*   **Ecclesiastical Governance (Catholic Church)**: If your current query involves the rather intricate, and some might argue, perpetually ancient, administrative structures of the [Catholic Church](/Pastoral_council), you are almost certainly looking for information pertaining to a [Pastoral council](/Pastoral_council). These bodies are, as their name subtly implies, concerned with the pastoral care and spiritual guidance within a given parish, offering counsel and collaboration to the parish priest. They are, predictably, not to be confused with local government bodies, a distinction that seems to elude many outside of their specific purview. Their function is rooted in the spiritual well-being and community life of the faithful, advising on matters of worship, evangelization, and service, rather than, say, waste collection schedules.

